declarations.comments:
Decodes an `ArrayBufferView` with the given `Encoding`.
Returns an `Error` if decoding fails.
declarations.title: decode

declarations.comments:
Decodes a UTF-8 encoded typed array to a (UTF-16) `String`.
Returns an `Error` if decoding fails.
This function is provided as a convenience as UTF-8 is the
encoding you will probably be using most of the time.
declarations.title: decodeUtf8

declarations.comments:
Possible character encodings.
For further information see
https://encoding.spec.whatwg.org/#names-and-labels
declarations.title: Encoding

declarations.comments: Encodes a `String` to a `Uint8Array` with the given `Encoding`.
declarations.title: encode

declarations.comments:
Encodes a `String` to a `Uint8Array` using UTF-8 encoding.
This function is provided as a convenience as UTF-8 is the
encoding you will probably be using most of the time.
declarations.title: encodeUtf8

declarations.comments:
Possible character encodings.
For further information see
https://encoding.spec.whatwg.org/#names-and-labels
declarations.title: Encoding
